flipSdpObject(25.10)                                      flipSdpObject(25.10)

Name
       flipSdpObject  -  Flips an SDP group on X or Y axis along with its ele-
       ments

Syntax
       flipSdpObject

       [-help]

       -object <object_name_list>

       [-x | -y ]

       Flips an SDP group on X or Y axis along with its elements.  The  align-
       ment information (justifyBy) is adjusted accordingly.

       Use  the flipSdpObject command when flipping can reduce wire length. In
       the traditional SDP flow, this command can be used while  defining  SDP
       constraints or while analyzing SDP alignment.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each flipSdpObject parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man flipSdpObject.

       -object <object_name_list>
              Specifies the names of the SDP groups to be flipped.

       -x | -y
              Specifies the axis on which the specified group (along with  its
              elements) should be flipped.

              Default: -y

Examples
              * The following command flips the SDP group sdpGrp1 on Y axis.

                flipSdpObject -object sdpGrp1

